T1  - Variable-rate deposit insurance: A re-examination
AU  - Goodman, Laurie S.
AU  - Santomero, Anthony M.
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 10
IS  - 2
SP  - 203
EP  - 218
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/06/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(86)90005-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426686900051
AB  - This paper investigates the impact of variable-rate deposit insurance on the financial and real sectors of the economy and its role as an absorber of bankruptcy risk within these sectors. A variable-rate system raises the cost of funds to the real sector and increases probability of bankruptcy of the borrowing firms. When such bankruptcies occur, society experiences a dead weight loss. We argue that appropriate deposit insurance pricing must weigh the social costs connected with both financial firm failure and real-sector bankruptcy.
ER  - 
